<div class="p">Conscious, he shakes his head, with rippling mane,</div>
<div class="p">For Mr. Muscle is a fop and vain,</div>
<div class="p">His jaw clear-chiseled, and a god's physique.</div>
<div class="p">A morning mist bedews each lovely cheek</div>
<div class="p">Of a sweet goddess, starting from repose</div>
<div class="p">As starts a kitten when a zephyr blows.</div>
<div class="p">And grace plays softly o'er her lustrous face,</div>
<div class="p">For she's a manufactory of grace.</div>
<div class="p">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; They prosecute the business of the day,</div>
<div class="p">Rent hard apart by solace and dismay;</div>
<div class="p">The lines of worry blazoned in their face,</div>
<div class="p">But softening with the latest on the race;</div>
<div class="p">Until the clock shows half eleven past,</div>
<div class="p">And sunshine breaks into their world at last.</div>
<div class="p">Two strangers dash into the street, embrace,</div>
<div class="p">And share congratulations on the race.</div>
<div class="p">But vast event our vision whirls away</div>
<div class="p">To sights of frantic millions in array</div>
<div class="p">Who flood the streets, do a generic dance,</div>
<div class="p">And look like long-legged spiders in a trance.</div>
<div class="p">See love and tolerance the severed head</div>
<div class="p">Raise on a pike with ghastly stains of red.</div>
<div class="p">Benevolence itself burns effigies,</div>
<div class="p">And justice celebrates with the Chinese.</div>
<div class="p">See harassed liberal professors saunter;</div>
<div class="p">And Steven Pinker dance beside a flaunter;</div>
<div class="p">He trusts but one authority, his REASON,</div>
<div class="p">Except the media in election season.</div>
<div class="p">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; See prodigies go flaming through the air;</div>
<div class="p">Two stars align, a most unusual pair,</div>
<div class="p">A star that died a thousand years ago,</div>
<div class="p">And a bright star new-born and all aglow.</div>
<div class="p">And mathematical moon-children writhe,</div>
<div class="p">And wake into the night, a morning tithe</div>
<div class="p">For standing timber, ancient as the church,</div>
<div class="p">Established as a much graffitied birch.</div>
<div class="p">Perplexing numbers mount, and sway between</div>
<div class="p">The counties as the grasses of a green:</div>
<div class="p">Numbers grotesque! which leer with bulbous faces,</div>
<div class="p">And are as plastic as Corona cases.</div>
<div class="p">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The sick, rise, walk embrace upon the street;</div>
<div class="p">Two people press on the verge of six feet;</div>
<div class="p">More miracles, say sources, are assured:</div>
<div class="p">He's just elected and the plague is cured!</div>
<div class="p">Throngs shifting hazily mass and unmass;</div>
<div class="p">Oceanic billows of dark floating gas</div>
<div class="p">Could no more threading, drifting, riffling, part,</div>
<div class="p">Then rush as sucked upon their unseen heart.</div>
<div class="p">The feckless motion beggars copious air:</div>
<div class="p">There faints a councilman, here swoons a mayor.</div>
<div class="p">Hear babble mount unto a heady roar,</div>
<div class="p">Then cease in concert vast across the corps.</div>
<div class="p">The hushed crowd parts, his reverence appears,</div>
<div class="p">Alumnus wise of profitable years,</div>
<div class="p">Crowned with the laurels of benignant age,</div>
<div class="p">And known in foreign circles as a sage.</div>
<div class="p">Admiring murmurs pierce the reigning hush,</div>
<div class="p">As silence is whelmed in a sudden rush;</div>
<div class="p">These voices compliment his coordination,</div>
<div class="p">Those say he runs well, why not run the nation?</div>
